Date: Sat, 18 Jan 2025 09:55:29 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] Fix accidental G3 character modification

The internally used unicode representation of G1 characters uses bit 5
(`0x20`) to indicate whether the separated or the contiguous form of the
particular character is meant. For G3 smooth mosaic and line drawing
characters, there is no such distinction.

When parsed Enhanced Teletext features are flushed, the mentioned bit is
(re)set for all graphical characters i.e. for both G1 and G3 characters.
In the G3 case, this accidentally modifies the requested G3 character
value.

Therefore limit the bit 5 manipulation to G1 characters only.

Fixes #20.
---
 src/teletext.c | 3 ++-
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/teletext.c b/src/teletext.c
index 1e8836d..e6145e8 100644
--- a/src/teletext.c
+++ b/src/teletext.c
@@ -1281,7 +1281,8 @@ enhance_flush(struct enhance_state *es, int column)
 			if (!es->mac.unicode)
 				es->ac.unicode = c.unicode;
 
-			if (vbi_is_gfx(es->ac.unicode)) {
+			/* G1 block mosaic character */
+			if (vbi_is_gfx(es->ac.unicode) && es->ac.unicode < 0xEF00) {
 				if (u)
 					es->ac.unicode &= ~0x20; /* separated */
 				else
